First, you probably downloaded the wrong bundle.  You&#39;ve downloaded the 
Heritrix source code. With the source tar ball, you will have to first 
compile all of the Heritrix source before you have a binary to run.  
This requires you install other software (maven).   I&#39;m guessing you 
want the binary version, the version that doesn&#39;t require a compile.  
Its named the same minus the &#39;-src&#39; snippet: i.e. heritrix-1.10.1.tar.gz.

The &#39;%&#39; in the above is meant to represent your command-line prompt.  Do 
not include it when you run the command local.  Type &#39;tar xfz 
heritrix-1.10.1.tar.gz&#39; only.


&gt;
&gt; how do we get past this very first step - extracting the tar.gz file
&gt; to where the files neeed to be?
&gt;
&gt; i use ssh log in su passowrd ... and then get to the temp dir cd /tmp
&gt;






There seems to be a bit of a misunderstanding.  I do not follow how your 
are picking up your need to ssh anywhere.


&gt; if somebody could walk me thru this, as if i were a six year old --
&gt; i would be very grateful !!!
&gt;



May I suggest that you get some help from a friendly unix geek who knows 
the web?  Heritrix is a fairly complex piece of software.  If you are 
having trouble installing, I&#39;m fairly certain that what follows -- the 
setup, running and analysis of the crawl product -- will prove trying.

Yours,
